column40:
Hello All,

Files are not getting picked up after running the Svjs PARES service and archived into OneDMS ScanView

Actual: The files are not getting picked up after running the SvjsPARES service in Service manager.
Expected: The file should be picked after running SVJSPares and archive into OneDMS ScanView.

*Steps to Re-produce:*
1. Login to Omnius via retail channel.
2. Check Serviceability.
3. Add Any package.
4. Proceed to checkout.
5. Fill in required details.
6. Generate contract documents.
7. Submit the order and send it for pares processing.

These connection parameters are still configured to use SID but this needs to be changed to use Service Name instead.

jdbc:oracle:thin:@10.0.51.90:1521:soconlrdb

column1: Old Reference OS-55090 OSF | Wave 8.2.1 | ACC1 | Incomplete OGW logs generated- Logs of Multiple services is not visible in OGW
column40:
We have observed that Multiple services logs are not getting generated in ogw.
We have created below table to track which services are visible and which services are not visible in ogw logs.
We have checked this issue for frequent used services, please find below observation.
|SOAP Action|Flow Name|Server Name|ACC2|ACC1|
|CreateFNPOrderStatus|New Activation FN|WF|Yes|No(Only response is visible)|
|SetFNOrderStatus|New Activation FN|WS|Yes|No|
|SetOrderStatus|New Activation All stacks|WS/WF|Yes|Yes|
|Fast Search|New Activation All stacks|WF|Yes|No|
|Save Document|New Activation All stacks|WF|No|No|
|GetProductAvailability|New Activation FN|WS|Yes|Yes|
|SendDocument|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetIdentMethods|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|SetPermission|Activation and ILS for All stacks|WS/WF|Yes|Yes|
|SubmitOrder|Activation and ILS for All stacks|WS/WF|Yes|Yes|
|GetOrder|Mobile New Activation (Retail)|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetOrderList|Mobile New Activation (Retail)|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetOrder4Archiving|Retail New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetDocuments|Retail New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|VFDECustomerSearch|Customer search for All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|OnOrderStatusChange |New Activation FN|WS|Yes|Yes|
|Tivano Input and Output|New Activation FN|WS|Yes|No|
|/MFTariffSoc-002/GetTariffSOCFeature|Mobile Customer Search|WS|Yes|Yes|
|/CustomerAccount-002/SearchCustomerBANSubscriber|Mobile Customer Search|WS|Yes|Yes|
|/BankAccountUtility-001/ValidateAndConvert|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|/MFMultipleSocs-001/MaintainSoc|Mobile Change Tariff|WF|Yes|yes|
|/HardwareOrder-001/GetAvailableShippingOptions|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|

 

 

Steps to reproduce: 
 # Login to omnius in telesales/retail channel in ACC1
 # place any order
 # submit the order
 # observe the issue in ogw

 

Expected result: All services logs should get printed in OGW

Actual result: Mulitple services logs is not getting printed in OGW.

column1: OSF | ACc1 ACC2 ACC3 | Wave 8.2.2 | Regression | Customer Identification Options are not getting enabled based on the HW Price Range
column40:
Performing New Activation Mobile we observed that Customer Identifications options are not getting enabled within mentioned range.

 

In Omnius, calculate the Ident method visibility based on total HW price in Order

e.g.
|*Total HW Price Range*|*Possible ident*|
|0-1000 €|All Ident possible|
|1000-1200 €|Only Store & Web Ident; (Hide/Disable?) Door Ident|
|greater than 1200 €|Only Web ident|

 

From <https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-313>

 

With a  (mobile) shopping cart value smaller than 1.199 EUR the following ident methods are available in checkout:
 * Min 0€ / Max 1.199€
 * Online-Ident
 * Store-Ident
 * Door-Ident

With value higher 1.199 EUR
 * Online-Ident
 * Store Ident

 

 

Steps Reproduce:

1) Login to Telesales using BO agent

2) Configure the package and select HW with 0-1000 euros and check if we get mentioned or define all 4 customer identification options during checkout in customer identification section

 

Actual Result

Currently if we select any HW within Defined range we see unexpected behavior during checkout in Customer identification section and its not working as expected following below table rules
|*Total HW Price Range*|*Possible ident*|
|0-1000 €|All Ident possible|
|1000-1200 €|Only Store & Web Ident; (Hide/Disable?) Door Ident|
|greater than 1200 €|Only Web ident|

 

Expected Result:

HW selected from Configurator should show the number of options in customer identification section accordingly following the below table
|*Total HW Price Range*|*Possible ident*|
|0-1000 €|All Ident possible|
|1000-1200 €|Only Store & Web Ident; (Hide/Disable?) Door Ident|
|greater than 1200 €|Only Web ident|
column232: HW selected within mentioned range does not show the respective customer identification option in section

column1: NEW CR OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.2 | sliding prices are not interpreted as expected
column40:
{color:#ff0000}The priority is set to "Blocker" as the issue is a show stopper for the Go Live of : [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-79] 
Without a fix the feature can not be deployed into production.{color}

 

Test data:

Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1 
Channel: Telesales + Retail

Steps to reproduce the issue:
 - Enter address: Goethestr. 27 26409 Wittmund Wittmund
 - Select package: "Kabel Internet & Phone"
 - Select tariff: "[3BV:B09] GigaZuhause 250 Kabel, 1.-9. Monat 19,99 €"
 - Select goody on "Gutschriften und Aktionen" section: "[JL5] Gutschrift GigaZuhause Young: 1.-9. Monat: 0 €, 10.-24. Monat: -5 €, danach 0 €"
 - open basket

The prices are not calculated as expected.
As a consequence of the wrong basket also the contract summary is incorrect.

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=856,height=463!  

+Pre-Analyses of product configuration team:+
OSF uses the 'Price sliding' field from the Product Catalog to configure the way the price periods are shown in the frontend:

!screenshot-1.png|width=338,height=226!

The numbers in this field are however interpreted as absolute points in time. They should however be interpreted as relative time intervals.

+Concretely this means:+

Price sliding '9:6:' should be interpreted as 0.-9. month, 10.-15. month, 16. month onward.
Currently it is interpreted as 0.-9. month, 0.-6. month, whatever comes afterward.
This obviously does not make any sense, since the second period ends before the first one, so the consequence in the frontend is, that the second period is ignored.

+The obvious fix therefore is:+
The numbers in the "Price sliding" field should always be interpreted as *relative time* intervalls.

 

+Additional proof:+
When checking in the OSF Backoffice for the product properties, the price_sliding of JL5 looks like this:

!image-2024-04-09-15-34-39-869.png!

Looking at this in overview in the frontend, the second time intervall seems to be ignored:

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=423,height=229!

Manually changing it to 15 then leads to the following view in OSF:

!image-2024-04-09-15-42-29-039.png|width=737,height=206!

This is, however, still wrong. OSF seems to tread the numbers in the PCAT import as absolute times instead of relative intervals

=> Three sliding prices are in principle possible to show, but the configuration in the product setup is imported and interpreted wrongly

column1: OSF | Wave8.2.1 | ACC3 | Sky is not sending updates to OGW after resuming sky ticket with "Failed-NoResume" from sky tool.
column40:
We have observed for every Order when agent is taking action from sky tool for Failed- NO Resume activity, Logs are not getting generated from Sky due to this issue order is not resuming in OGW.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Submit order.
2. Sky ticket generated.
3. Resume sky ticket with Failed no Resume.
4. Logs (Request) not generated.

Actual: Sky is not sending request to OGW after resuming sky ticket with "Failed" from sky tool.

Expected: Sky should send request to OGW after resuming sky ticket with "Failed" from sky tool.

Test data:

Omnius Order id: 
 |431543|
|431537|

column804:
15/Apr/24 7:43 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;Comment from Vishank :

Hi All,

 

As discussed and suggested by Dev team in today’s meeting, need to update and add the value for below tags in *“property_env_ACC3.xml”* file for O2A WF module. (WF_1 & WF_2)  -- as executor message stuck in jms queue. (from defect bridge chat)

 

*In common section :-*

<WF_DISPATCHER_NUM>10</WF_DISPATCHER_NUM>

<WF_EXECUTER_NUM>50</WF_EXECUTER_NUM>

 

*In WF_1 & WF_2 sections :-* 

<JAVA_MEM_ARGS>-Xms5g -Xmx5g -XX:CompileThreshold=8000 -XX:MetaspaceSize=512m  -XX:MaxMetaspaceSize=512m -XX:SurvivorRatio=2 -XX:+UseParallelGC -XX:+UseParallelOldGC -XX:SurvivorRatio=4 -XX:TargetSurvivorRatio=90 -XX:-UseAdaptiveSizePolicy -XX:+DisableExplicitGC -verbose:gc -XX:+PrintGCTimeStamps -XX:+PrintGCDetails -XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError -Xloggc:./logs/gc.log -Djdk.tls.client.protocols=TLSv1</JAVA_MEM_ARGS>

 

The above-mentioned changes require redeployment and restart of ACC3 O2A WF module.

 

*Note :-* The change in above parameters in above mentioned file (property_env_ACC3.xml{*}){*} are specific to ACC3 environment only. Also, it depends on the resources available on the specific environment servers. (here deosa12vr & 13vr);;;

column40:

!image-2024-03-26-13-28-55-505.png!

 

 

In above image OM recieved the request at 8:06:43 and OM responded at 8:36:36, so its almost taking 30 mins to respond.

 # go to CS -CD page
 # observe the issue

 

Expected result: CS-CD should be generated within a minute

Actual result: CS-CD is generating after 30 mins, due to OM responding late.

column823:
15/May/24 9:53 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

yes, currently the fix is almost ready after discussions with design team and Ketaki.

in this fix the 24 retry will not be in use anymore, instead the retry will be determined by the ogw_error_handler table.

it will decide how many times to retry, and how much time to wait between the calls.

for this flow the retry will be active for empty response from oneDMS or OGWERR-9900 error code return

for example:
this is a record from the table:

{
    "ERROR_CODE":"OGWERR-9900",
    "ERROR_CATEGORY":"Technical",
    "IGNORE_ERROR_IND":"N",
    "RETRYABLE_IND":"TRUE",
    "MAX_RETRY_TIMES":"3",
    "RETRY_WAIT_TIME":"10",
    "MAX_WAIT_TIME":null,
    "STATUS_TO_SET":null,
    "CHANNEL":"TELESALES",
    "SERVICE_CALL":"ASYNC",
    "SERVICE_NAME":"OneDMS"
}
so the flow will retry 3 times and the wait time will be 10 seconds between every try.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 KUD standalone products blocked in checkout after IBAN validation
column40:
Currently KUD TV products for Unitymedia as well as for VKD cannot be booked, as failing in checkout with error message after IBAN Validation.

Steps to reproduce for Telesales channel:

1) Enter unitymedia or VKD adress -> new customer
2) Add KUD product e.g. GigaTV Net, 1.{-}6. Monat 0,{-}€
3) move to checkout, fill in customer details > customer adress in Germany
4) reach to IBAN section, type in GERMAN IBAN e.g. DE20700500000003658888 (Any German IBAN can be taken!)
->IBAN validation is running and successfull
5) Select invoice adress as customer adress and do NOT select any different bank account holder
6) Klick on "weiter" and get error message

_{color:#ff0000}Die ausgewählten kabel-unabhängigen Produkte (z.B. GigaTV App und Net) lassen seit dem 01.04.2018 eine Nutzung innerhalb der gesamten EU zu. Aber nach gesetzlichen Vorgaben nur von Kunden mit festem Wohnsitz in Deutschland.){color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Die Prüfung der Bankverbindung hat ergeben, dass eine ausländische Bankverbindung oder ein abweichender Kontoinhaber angegeben wurden.{color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Leider kann aus diesen Gründen die Prüfung auf festen Wohnsitz in Deutschland nur über den nächsten Vodafone-Shop erfolgen. Bringen Sie hierzu Ihren Personalausweis oder eine Meldebescheinigung mit.{color}_

 

We are not using foreign customer adress or foreign IBAN, and also +*not*+ using foreign invoice adress or different bank account holder
It is not the problem, that its going to be validated if there is any data from foreign countries used! The validation itself is correct process - but the result is wrong! It has to be identified by the system, that this customer is allowed to pay the products so we are able to move to the next section.

 

It seems the booking works sometimes, and sometimes not. Or maybe only for specific constellation of KUD products it works. We need to investigate if there is an issue with the software or not

 

*Positive* examples from this morning:
ID: ** 801847; IAV Weboder ID: 6088191
OSF Order ID: 801861; IAV Weborder ID: 6088197

 

Please note: SAME issue is visible on ACC2, although there is still wave 8.1.5 code present!!

Please check possible side effects from CR780 Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandat which was one of the last production fixes and is available on both ACC

Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com]  [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] ,

We have analyzed further and found that there is recent requirement over (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-690) [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg!VFDED1FTS-5531: CR780 - Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandatIN DESIGN|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1FTS-5531] which is now available as part of the software where we are testing the above scenario.

As part the requirement we are now showing NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button of payment section if the scenario we are performing meets below conditions.

System will validate if payment method = "direct debit"
 * if yes: system will validate if IBAN = DE-IBAN

 ** if yes: system will validate if bank account owner (payer contact) = legal contact

 *** if yes: the system will validate if the bank account owner address (payer address) = legal address

 **** if yes: the system switches to the next checkout section

 **** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 *** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 ** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 * if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button.;;;

As per the CR780 we are checking below conditions

Technically we have only these additional validation

column808:
18/Apr/24 12:36 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;There was a meeting between Kshitij and Andreas with following outcome:
 * Values like "AccountCategory" in Omnius are derived from OGW: Here:- _AccountCategory_ in getCustomerResult for index search and _Region_ in retrieveCustomerInfo mode1 for LegacySearch.
 * As the ADDRESS REGION is in UM Area - it is treated as UM customer, even though he belongs to the VKD Stack

h4. _Possible SD option to be validated/proven:_ 
 * Derive customer stack from GlobalID prefix ("legacy stack")  instead of address region
 * IF improvements required as this is only known by OGW (Omnius can only see LK_ from linked customers) - e.g. introducing new attribute to indicate customers product stack:
 * CustomerSearch()
 * getCustomerDetails()
 * [@Mitra, Gaurab, External Vendor|mailto:gaurab.mitra@amdocs.com]: We should investigate if further interfaces have to be considered (To be discussed on next CR meeting)

[@Kshitij.Srivastava@comviva.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@comviva.com]: To check UseCases in Omnius to be considered for an improvement

Further benefit: Omnius Performance increase If product stack information is directly provided by OGW 

 

So team is working on possible solution but will take some time ;;;

24/Jan/24 3:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  I was not creating any order, I am just scanning portal UI tool from time to time to find unidentified issues. And within this quality check I have found tickets with this error message. 

 

After some analysis I have identified, that it seems to be this scenario:

-> Search existing unitymedia customer and perform Move to VKD adress 

 

this is example Order ID from ACC1 - it failed with 2 sky tickets

One ticket because of invalid VPKN (issue is solved, please ignore that) and second sky ticket was for setpermission.


Unfortunately Sky ticket were cleared in between so I am not able to find my two tickets anymore..... But hopefully you can reproduce on your environment for a Move from Unity to VKD.

Seems like in this case the existing customer ID from unity is taken over, instead of recognizing that customer will get a new customer ID from VKD for Move scenario

 

Order ID 782545, Customer ID 1009755201 (initial customer before Move) 

!image-2024-01-24-11-21-17-927.png!

 

Same seems to happen when moving from Unity Cable to DSL product. 

So please check flow Unity Cable to VKD Cable Move, and Unity Cable to DSL Move

 ;;;

Which means for the existing customer we are getting the region value from Install Base and if region value which is from the IB or from the serviceability(in ACQ) is not matching with the below table data which is agreed during the design, then OSE send empty <CustomerList><CustomerDetails>{*}<TargetSystem>{*}.

18/Apr/24 12:37 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;There was a meeting between Kshitij and Andreas, with following comment:
 * Customers region value is received from Install Base (<CustomerList><CustomerDetails><{*}TargetSystem{*}>).
 * As this is a MOVE scenario, the IB Region value is from the former residence (which is VKD) of the customer and therefore does not match the future address (which is UM)
 * SOLUTION: Add address check for future target residence/address of the customer

h4. _It may be the case that this is a bug, as future target resicence/address should already be checked per design_
 * [@Kshitij.Srivastava@comviva.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@comviva.com]: Please check/verify design for setPermission in move scenario.;;;

column40:

Env ACC1

Place an order in ACC1

Check whether the map is available

column232: Delivery option: Delivery to pack station can only be selected via list and not via map
column477:
The Maps JavaScript API team regularly updates the API with new features, bug fixes, and performance improvements. 

As part of this activity some older version of the Maps JavaScript API version are deprecated. Currently its corrected by using version which is available.

Issue might reoccur if Maps JavaScript API deprecate the currently used version 

Solution: New keys have been supplied to T5D for the Map issue with different functionalities per Env. Now the Map is getting displayed for all ACC envs

column1: OSF | CR716 Wave8.2 | ACC1 | Unitymedia | Error message is displayed in Access details if order placed in NE3 Address with self install =no
column40:

in Access details we are getting the below error

({*}Your technical connection selection does not match){*}

3)checkout and move forward

4)check whether any error message is shown in Access Details

 

Actual: Error message is shown at access details page

Expected: No error message should be shown in Access details page 

Note:If we change the access details option to technician required for TV product then we are able to move forward without any issue

column40:
test environment: test1b /ACC2 Wave 8.1

Scenario: 
Existing Unitymedia cable customer with following inventory: legacy KIP Product (not Broadvision) and legacy TV Product (Code UMDKLM) orders GigaZuhause 1000 (Broadvision product) - Telesales

column782:
09/Nov/23 7:56 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;From what I can see in VkdGateway the price of the product is correctly returned as:

"nonStandardRate": 17.64, 

which with VAT makes ~20.99€.

The product itself however does not seem to indicate that it has a price nor a non standard rate, both of which should however not be necessary for unity inventory products.

It is noteworthy that the product itself has no price configured in the product setup, maybe the display in the contract summary of OSF does not work if it is an inventory product without a price (and without a non standard rate actually configured in the product setup)?

To me this sounds a) like an OSF issue and b) not like a BV issue.;;;

column785: 27/Sep/23 3:35 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I am currently trying to reproduce it on a cloud sandbox to gain more insight what actually happens on OSF side, maybe [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] could rerun a testcase on an ACC environment with logging enabled as outlined on [How to get acc logs - Portals - Vodafone DE Confluence|https://de.confluence.agile.vodafone.com/display/PORTALS/How+to+get+acc+logs]?;;;
column786:
27/Sep/23 5:11 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I tested this on one of our cloud sandboxes with v9.17.0-BB123 and cable PCAT V2301_2023_10_00_020 with the mock [Cable_Address_Availability_KIP500_SI.|https://ash-sb5-telesales.osf.paps-vf.de/agent/account/login?showProductCodes=true&TC_ID=Cable_Address_Availability_KIP500_SI]

Result: during the checkout I can select 1V1 as a TV technician and TECYESKIP as a KIP technician.
The logs indicate that 1V1 is never passed to cable product logic as selected.
I attached the log of the session.
[^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322.log]

The log should contain an entry like "1V1|true" which it does not.

I also reproduced the issue with the mock [Cable_Address_Type_NE4-VVO|https://ash-sb5-telesales.osf.paps-vf.de/agent/account/login?showProductCodes=true&TC_ID=Cable_Address_Type_NE4-VVO] which results in VP0 being selectable in the checkout. Again in the log we cannot find VP0 ever being passed to the cable product logic as selected.

[^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322_VP0.log]

At this point I think this is a OSF bug, since cable logic cannot control when and with which products it is called by OSF.;;;
column788:
29/Sep/23 3:00 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Hi Vikash,
as the logs show the PCAT returns VP0 and 1V1 as visible in this case, so maybe we have a different understanding what "visible" in this case means?
My understanding of visible in this case is:
 * the last call of the cable rules plugin by osf returns a list of packages, each containing a list of products.
 * a product is "visible" for a dropdown if the property "visible" in the last return value of the cable rules plugin for this particular product was "true".

 ** this is especially distinct from the "visibility" of tariffs in the configurator which depends on more information like:
 *** is the product selected
 *** is it configured to be shown in the configurator
 *** is the product "visible" according to the last result of the cable rules plugin

*According to the logs 1V1/VP0 is visible in this case but is never selected by OSF even if the agent selects it in the dropdown*

This is even underlined by the fact that 1V1/VP0 are shown in the dropdown {*}which would not be the case if the were not "visible"{*}.;;;

column795:
10/Oct/23 3:58 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;The cause for the skyticket or the cable backend error is the missing VP0/1V1 product. This is missing because, according to our investigation, the product is never passed to the cable product logic in OSF, even if the corresponding dropdown is selected in the OSF checkout.

Hi [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] ,
thank you for the investigation.
According to our investigation we do not have any Compatibility Rules that deselect 1V1, and as said before 1V1 also never appears in the input to the cable rules plugin. 
Also check this previous comment for a log: https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-44322?focusedId=2949361&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2949361

As things stand there is nothing cable logic can do to deselect the product as the product is never select from the point of view of the cable product logic.

Please investigate on your side why 1V1 is never passed to CREP as selected once it is selected in the shopping cart/checkout.

Best regards

Simon;;;
column796: 10/Oct/23 4:24 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;Hi [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] if the root cause is the missing VP0/ 1V1, why in the bug OS-44216 no Sky Ticket is created. There VP0 is also not booked. Thank you;;;
column797:
10/Oct/23 8:12 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com], if the order fails or not depends on the other contents of the order and if the missing VP0 and 1V1 cause a conflict in the ibp. Not all orders behave the same in this regard.
I think it is likely (but not necessary) that this bug and OS-44216 have the same root cause in OSF.;;;
column798:
11/Oct/23 1:52 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;h3. SunilkumarCM added a comment - 
 
 
Hi [~simon.auch@vodafone.com]  ,

This issue on Sky or Cable backend we talking above may be related to CR676. Check with VF as we don't have any implementation on OSE for CR676.

Also we have some discussions going on for CR676 with on [OS-44236] SIT1 | Retail/Telesales | CR676 | Cable order is failing with error JSON validation failure - Vodafone Global Jira

[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] fyi;;;
column799:
11/Oct/23 2:53 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Hi Vikash,

I do not think it is related to CR676 as it has nothing to do with the json schema, but a change in that CR could of course have impacted OSE to behave differently. According to my knowledge however CR676 only had OGW impact until recently and should have no impact whatsoever on OSE and with which products OSE calls the cable product logic.

As I said before, from our perspective there is absolutely nothing cable can do about this *because we do not control with which products cable product logic is called by from OSE.*

*Please investigate in OSE why the cable product logic is not called with the product after it is selected in the checkout.* Before this is done there will be nothing we can do to help with this issue, so please refrain to assigning it back to me before this is investigated. If you have further question please set up a meeting with me.

Best regards

Simon;;;

column811:
06/Dec/23 8:20 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I further analysed this issue and found the following:

Orders created by OSF contain a field 
{code:json}
"apartmentDetails":{"technicianNeeded":
true/false
}
{code}
As far as I can tell from tests the field is always true if and only if the agent selected the technician_yes option in either the TV or the KIP dropdown during the checkout.

This information should also be passed to the cable rules plugin, in the field `IServiceAddress::technicianNeeded`.

After the selection of technician options in the dropdown the cable posting rules are executed again by OSF, but the the `technicianNeeded` field is not set to true (as it should be if the agent previously selected VP0/TECYESKIP in the technician dropdowns).

This can be checked by searching for `technicianNeeded` in the following log: [^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322_technicianNeeded.log] 
Notice that the last execution contains `TECYESKIP|true`, since the agent selected the kip technician to be necessary.

For fixing this bug the cable rules artifact logs can be used to check if the technician needed flag is passed to the cable rules plugin correctly.
In the meantime we will try to provide a workaround that might resolve most of the issues as well. We have an experimental workaround since version V2330_2024_01_00_032.
Until this issue is fixed on OSF side and we can remove our workaround again I would keep this ticket open however.;;;

10/Jan/24 9:28 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 

Okay, let me go through your message step by step.

For the first test case:
 * I can reproduce it :)
 * I think that only the TV dropdown is shown is correct (according to the up to now still best documentation we have: [Scenario dimension "Technician appointment" - OSF - Vodafone Global Confluence|https://confluence.sp.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=103985437]).
 * I think VP0 being selectable is also correct (again according to above documentation, and to some tests we have [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#216-236]).
 * VP0 disappearing afterwards sounds problematic and without investigating I have no idea why it would.
 ** VP0 not being selected anymore however explains that my workaround doesn't work because it relied on the presence of the technician options instead of the flag.

For the second case:
 * I can reproduce the behaviour :)
 * I don't understand the problem with this though? For this particular example you can proceed either with no technician at all (TECNOKIP, TECNOTV are both selectable) or with a technician (TECYESKIP, 1V1 can be selected together).
 * If the issue is the error message, what would be the expected behaviour if a different technician selection would be made by the agent?
 * If the issue is that the TV dropdown is visible at all: that confuses me a bit as well, since our tests would indicate that only the kip options should be shown in this case: [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#239-259]

column40:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

Test address: Ottobrunner Str. 55 81737 München (NE4-VVO)

 

{color:#172b4d}*Please note:*{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}first we thought the Sky Error is related to KIP only, but if we create an order with KIP only on the same address, there is no Sky Error, e. g.: OSF Order ID: 999881{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}on NE3 addresses the bug does not appear:{color}

{color:#172b4d}!image-2023-09-22-13-58-49-056.png!{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}on ACC1 the bug does also appear:{color}

{color:#172b4d}!image-2023-09-22-13-39-25-797.png!{color}

 

 

{+}Actual result{+}: KIP Technician field for orders with TV and KIP is missing on NE4-VVO addresses

 

+Expected result:+ KIP Technician field for orders with TV and KIP should be displayed

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load an ENV address, e. g.: Ottobrunner Str. 55 81737 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select a TV tariff, e. g.: "[CKH8] Vodafone TV Cable"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select a TV tariff, e. g.: "[01H:B06] GigaZuhause 1000 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

 

– > the field "Anschluss (WE) is bereits sehbereit / aktiv" is missing 

 

!image-2023-09-22-12-01-00-237.png!

column782:
27/Sep/23 2:24 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I am not aware of any interface that lets cable control the display of whole dropdown sections. The answer why the whole section is missing can only be given by OSF.

If I had to guess I would assume OSF is hardcoded to check for TECYESKIP, TECNOKIP, UMTECKIP:NOO, UMTECKIP:YES. One of the relevant tests in our test suite is likely:
{code:java}
    Scenario: New cable TV (KAA) and KIP customer without self-install on NE4-VVO address
        Given a KDG service address where "analog and digital" TV is available with object category "NE4-VVO"
        And a KDG service address where internet with data transfer rate "1000" is available
        And self-install is 'not available'
        And a selection
            | productCode |
            | TC2         |
            | 01H:B06     |
        When I get the availability and basket
        Then the products have the states
            | productCode  | state         |
            | TC2          | selected      |
            | 01H:B06      | selected      |
            | TECNOKIP     | not available |
            | TECYESKIP    | not available |
            | TECNOTV      | not available |
            | TECYESTV     | not available |
            | VP0          | selectable    |
            | 1V1          | not available |
            | UMTECKIP:NOO | not available |
            | UMTECKIP:YES | not available | {code}
According to my understanding no kip technician is needed at VVO addresses since the TV technician will handle the installation.
As with the other bug tickets I think we need clarification from business what the expected behaviour is.

 ;;;

column786:
21/Sep/23 5:30 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;*Guess:* 
Cable product logic tries to rebuild the selection of the agent in each step. This means that certain clickflows are not really supported.

If their are for example two products A and B, A is visible, B is not, selecting A replaces A with B.
If the agent now selects A, A will be added to the selection and the product logic will replace it with B, the agent will see B in the selection.
If the cable product logic is executed again B is not a valid selection because it is not visible.

In this case A would be VP0, and B would be 1V1.

I do not think that there is a simple fix for this issue if my guess is correct.

The two options I see:
 # do not restrict the visibility of VP0 in this case
 ** this would imply that the agent could directly select VP0
 ** since VP0 and 1V1 are mapped to the same dropdown option in OSF -> the agent can only select VP0 together with 1V1, the replacement of 1V1 with VP0 then actually just removes 1V1 since VP0 is already selected.
 # maybe 1V1 should not be selectable in the first place
 ** instead of allowing the agent to select 1V1 which will automatically be replaced with VP0 allow the agent to select VP0 directly instead.

*Open questions:*

Which option is preferred by business?
 * if option 2 is preferred: should this also applied to other portals

What exactly are the affected cases? 
 * likely all test cases where the rule that replaces 1V1 with VP0 applies. 
 * Can business confirm that all cases affected by the rule below should be changed with either option 1 or 2?
 * The rule is: 

{code:java}
Rule 'Replace_1V1_with_VP0_when_ordering_KAI':
When
    selected products contain '1V1' and
    condition 'new_kip_order' applies and
    condition 'digitalSelected' applies
then
    deselect '1V1' and
    select 'VP0' with contract relation set to the main analog product. {code}
 ;;;

thank you for the investigation.
According to our investigation we do not have any Compatibility Rules that deselect 1V1, and as said before 1V1 also never appears in the input to the cable rules plugin. 
For completeness we attach the log of the cable rules plugin so you can check for yourself that 1V1 is never passed to the cable product logic as selected: [^cable_rules_artifact372637.log] 

When working with the log searching for "1V1|true" and "1V1|false" returns the corresponding input state of the product. You will find that no entry exist for "1V1|true".

As things stand there is nothing cable logic can do to deselect the product as the product is never select from the point of view of the cable product logic.

Please investigate on your side why 1V1 is never passed to CREP as selected once it is selected in the shopping cart (as seen in one of your screenshots).

Best regards

Simon;;;

column1: Execution of Defaulted-Obligated rules is not working correctly for mutually-exclusive category
column40:
we are currently struggeling with the following business requirement.

We have a mutually-exclusive category X ( here: access hardware)

 

If any of this Product A of X is chosen than a Product P (here: Product 10004 Shipping_Fee) should be Defaulted.

Only Exception: if Product B of X (here: Eigenhardware) is choosen, than Product P should not be added

 

We build a rule (here: CR006048)

If not B than defaulted-obligated P (Prio 6)
 
First Result:

If we switch from A to B P stay in the cart

 

I added an additional Prio 1 rule: If P is in the cart -> Do not allow P.

 

Result:

If we switch from A to B P is removed, which is fine.

But if I switch back from B to A I get the error

{color:#FF0000}*Die folgenden Produkte: [10004] Versandkosten können nicht hinzugefügt werden weil sie mit der aktuellen Auswahl nicht kombinierbar sind.*{color}

 

+*Expected Result:*+

Product 10004 should be defaulted or removed just by the rule CR006048, no other rule neccessary

 

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

*-ProcessContext ACQ*
 # *Enter any address.*
 #  *Choose any tarif -> A hardware is defaulted*
 # *Switch to hardware Eigenhardware*
 # *Switch back to any other access hardware -> error message is shown*

 

*Details:*

*Defaulted-Obligated - Rule*
{code:java}
<SourceConditions>
    <Aggregator>any</Aggregator>
    <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    <ConditionName>Versandkosten added during ACQ_7994</ConditionName>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProductInCategory</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="categoryID">FN169</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProduct</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">20099900_sub</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>false</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
</SourceConditions>
<TargetConditions>
    <TargetAggregator/>
    <ConditionValue/>
    <ConditionName>Product 10004</ConditionName>
    <TargetCondition>
        <Type>Product</Type>
            <Params>
                <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
            </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </TargetCondition>
</TargetConditions>
<Operation askconfirmationfirst="false" overrideinitialselectable="false">Defaulted-Obligated</Operation>
<Priority>6</Priority>{code}
 
*NOT-ALLOW-Rule*
{code:java}
<SourceConditions>
    <Aggregator>all</Aggregator>
    <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    <ConditionName>Cart contains Versandkosten 10004_8511</ConditionName>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProduct</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
</SourceConditions>
<TargetConditions>
    <TargetAggregator/>
    <ConditionValue/>
    <ConditionName>Product 10004</ConditionName>
    <TargetCondition>
        <Type>Product</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </TargetCondition>
</TargetConditions>
<Operation askconfirmationfirst="false" overrideinitialselectable="false">Not Allowed</Operation>
<Priority>1</Priority>{code}

First of all we have found a workaround to make this particular business rule working.

The example here is:

We have a (initial) default rule. If agent selects tariff A default hardware P. Of course this rule is true also in further runs of compRules

Agent switches manually to other hardware Q of this mutually exclusive category

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1 | CR716 Futurize regression defect | when booking ES5 on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, Self install is selected  in the access details for Unity Orders
column40:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

VKD address: Alte Post 1 44869 Bochum (ABK = no; Selfinstall = yes)

!image-2023-09-06-13-09-31-974.png!

select the Experten-Service Einrichtung for any Broadband Order:

Check the Access details section:

!image-2023-09-06-13-13-05-731.png!

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking Experten-Service Einrichtung on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, self install  is available in the access details

+Expected result:+ when booking Experten-Service Einrichtung on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, Technician  should be available in access details

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * create a new customer on a UM address where ABK = no, and Selfinstall = yes, E.G:Alte Post 1 44869 Bochum
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"

 * select any KIP tariff, e. g.: GigaZuhause 100 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on "Optionen"
 * select  {*}Experten-Service Einrichtung{*}" ({+}with this option a technician is booked{+})
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * fill in the customer data
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > Check which option is selected in Access details

Note:Backend is selecting the technician as expected:

!image-2023-09-06-13-28-30-763.png|width=483,height=125!

OSF:RETAIL:ACC2:Omnius ID:991759

OGW:2695200

CN:1002969303

Unity Backend

Expected: The modem hardware 20090213 is not an IAD, it's only an "Hardware Zubehör"/secondary hardware, it should be deselecable, once the customer wanted.

PCAT rule configuration: CR005943 GF Modem defaulted if it is not in installedBase and no FritzBox 5590 existing

But even though, the product 20090213 cannot be deselected.
The software team must fix this issue, so the target product 20090213 is going to be put into shopping cart as default, but could be deselected anytime by agent if necessary.

column786:
10/Nov/23 12:34 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Hari Shankar Malviya added a comment - 
 
 
Hi [~shuyan.luo@vodafone.com]  ,

Based on the code investigation, it appears that this is not a issue, the manual_override_allowed field value is 0 in the catalog_package_subtypes table which is why its not allowing to deselect the hardware.

When the PCAT files are imported, the values of this field are set according to the values available in the PCAT files, so if the PCAT file does not contain this filed value for any stack, the value is considered to be 0.

When the manual_override_allowed field is set to 1 for a fixed stack, then the hardware can be deselected in the configurator according to the value in the manual_override_allowed field.

!image-2023-11-10-12-33-31-352.png!;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1 | CR716 Futurize regression defect | when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV are not displayed
column40:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

*Please note: there was a change on PCAT side: [[PORPDT-345] BV - Removal of Ready-to-Watch (Sehbereitschaft) Section - DE Jira (vodafone.com)|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-345]*

*When booking first KIP then TV, the expected result should be:*
 # *the Access Details for TV should not be displayed*
 # {*}the Access Details for KIP should be displayed but without the technician option{*}{*}{{*}}

 

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV are not displayed

+Expected result:+ when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV should be also displayed

 

!image-2023-07-21-08-34-10-642.png|width=757,height=570!

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to ACC2 Retail
 * search for a Cable address, e. g.: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select any KIP tariff, e. g.: "GigaZuhause 1000 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select any TV tariff, e. g.: "Vodafone Basic TV Cable inklusive Endgerät (Angebot bei Neubestellung zusammen mit Vodafone TV Connect)"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

– > the access detail for KIP are displayed – > *OK*

– > the access detail for TV are NOT displayed – > *NOT OK*

*!image-2023-07-21-08-39-31-216.png|width=894,height=583!*

*When booking TV only on the same address the access details for TV are displayed*

21/Sep/23 4:32 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;In order to properly fix this I assume that cable and OSF will have to deliver a fix.

According to the answer from [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-42115?focusedId=2910953&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2910953 the display of the tv access details depends on the availability of the products TECNOTV and TECYESTV reported by the cable logic.

*Why does the workaround work?*

My *assumption* is that OSF remembers the availability of TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV from a previous execution of the cable logic.

If KIP is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return TECNOTV and TECYESTV as not available. 

If TV is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return either TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV as available.

-> This is something that has to be fixed by OSF

{*}What is the implication of the Workaround?{*}{*}{{*}}

Assuming cable product logic would return TECNOTV or TECYESTV as bookable the issue might persist in OSF, since as long as KIP is selected first TECNOTV and TECYESTV will still not be available from the start.

*Open questions from my perspective:*
 * which products exactly control the display of the tv access details in OSF?
 ** Is it only TECYESTV and TECNOTV or also products like VP0, 1V1?
 ** Is this controlled by special tags on products or categories, or are the products hardcoded in OSF?
Maybe [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] can answer this question?
 *  in which scenarios should which technician option be bookable in OSF?

 * 
 ** we have a list of ~80 test cases. Some of these are apparently not correct.
 ** Who can go through these test cases with us and determine which of them need to be changed?
 ** Without at least a contact person that can answer this question it will not make sense to start implementation of this ticket.

 ;;;

column812:
13/Jun/24 2:32 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi all,
so, PORPDT-345 will not make this requirement obsolete, it will just slightly shift how it looks.

The new requirements are: if only TV is ordered, show the section. If TV + Internet is ordered, don't show it.

The new problem is this:
If the agent books the packages in the following order
 * TV
 * KIP

then the TV accessibility section is shown, but it should not.

The problem is still the same as described by [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] in the comment from 21/Sep/2023: 
OSF seems only to decide on whether to show the accessibility section for TV when the TV package is opened. So,
 * we first open TV and book a TV Connect ---> OSF sees that 1V1 and TECNOTV are available and correctly assumes that it should show the TV accessibility section
 * we then open the internet section and book some GigaZuhause tariff ---> from now on, 1V1 and TECNOTV are not available anymore, but OSF seems to not update its opinion on the TV accessibility and will display it anyway
 * IF the user just simply opens the TV package again (without changing anything), OSF updates again and will correctly NOT display it

This is something we cannot fix and still need a change from OSF.;;;

column822:
01/Jul/24 7:38 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 
Thank you for the re-test.

The failure in case 2, where the technician option for KIP is wrongly displayed, is again the OSF bug discussed further below:
- when you book KIP first, then OSF calculates the technician option it wants to show for KIP, which is for a pure KIP order on an self-install address currently "Anschluss ist sehbereit".

- when you then book TV, it will not update the technician option it wants to show for KIP, and just show it regardless.

- when you just simply open the KIP package after the TV selection again, OSF _will_ update its opinion and not show the KIP technician section.

We cannot do anything here on our side and would need a fix from TechM side, so that OSF will always update both the TV and KIP technician section, no matter which package is currently opened.

 

About the "Verbindungsdaten speichern" field I don't know much unfortunately --neither how it is controlled nor what the desired logic behind it is.;;;
column824:
02/Jul/24 3:06 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}. 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package] KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package] TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package] Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package] TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;

column40:
In unity address new acquisition of KUD standalone via telesales is blocked.

*Steps to recreate:*

1)Place a new order in Telesales in NRW or KBW region.

Alexandra Vaduva added a comment -
 
 
Hi Harsha/Ari,

This was clear from the beginning, yes, but as I mentioned, the implementation was intended to be like this :

*In case of telesales, if sepa is true, then this check will be shown and the flow is blocked → agent is not able to continue*

Which means that it does *NOT* matter _what IBAN is used_ , this will be shown if the sepa is true and *If the KUD product is part of cable_app_de category .* 

I agree that the way this is working is not consistent : in one case the agent is able to continue but in another the agent is not able to continue.

The final question is - when should the agent be able to continue the checkout process and when should the agent be blocked? According to the initial documentation the agent should not be able to continue and according to these comments the agent should be able to continue .

What is the purpose of this error message and what was wrongly implemented exactly? We can implement a fix according to these comments but we need to know if the issue is that the whole implementation was not done correctly or not, in order to fix the actual issue and not just a particular case .;;;

We have analyzed further and found that there is recent requirement over (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-690) [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg!VFDED1FTS-5531: CR780 - Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandatIN DESIGN|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1FTS-5531] which is now available as part of the software where we are testing the above scenario.

As part the requirement we are now showing NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button of payment section if the scenario we are performing meets below conditions.

System will validate if payment method = "direct debit"
 * if yes: system will validate if IBAN = DE-IBAN

 ** if yes: system will validate if bank account owner (payer contact) = legal contact

 *** if yes: the system will validate if the bank account owner address (payer address) = legal address

 **** if yes: the system switches to the next checkout section

 **** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 *** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 ** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 * if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button.

column1: OSF | Wave7.1 | ACC1&ACC2 | Telesales | Unitymedia orders with manual approval do not reach status completed
column40:
In case unitymedia order is not approved automatically in RNS, we are missing the order status and customer number in OSF.

Steps:
 * start order for unitymedia in Telesales (e.g. with KIP)
 * Submit order and check weborder ID in IAV
 * Identify reference ID is created in unity backend but order is not approved automatically
 * Approve order with the given reference ID in unitymedia backend (No new order is created! Weborder ID is set as external reference)
 * Check status / customer number in VKD and OGW -> information for customer ID is missing and status is not completed

Expected:

Also for manual approved orders the status is set to completed and customer ID is transferred via VKD to OSF

column869:
07/Dec/23 1:51 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Updates:

 

OGW needs the customer number in case Unity Manual Approval Orders in Telesales and Retails, which should be provided from VKD to OGW within the existing FulfillmentStarted Request.

 

The customer number is atm provided only for Auto Approval Orders, but missing for Manual Approval orders, therefore the document cannot be archived and the OGW processing remain in status pending (the VKD status is SUCCESS but the orders don't get Sucecss status in OSF Fronend):

An error was encountered while invoking ScanView-SaveDocument WS. Details [Error_Code: HTTPOutbound_0001, Error_Message: Received a fault from processing server for service '/ScanView-001/SaveDocument': An invalid number format or number value was encountered.

Note: Retail Manual Approval Orders don't have this issue because the call to oneDMS/Customernumber is not needed for the E2E flow. They get the Status Success.

 

As the customer number has not been sent for Manual Approval Order until now, a new PST change is required.

I will take the topic with me and check if we can request this change at the PST CAT train, Team Ash(Benjamin Sachse) or Nora.

 

The new requirement should contain following information:
 * no difference between retail and telesales from cable perspective
 * example set status messages received by OSF
 * fulfilment started from manual approval 
 * fulfilment started from automatic approval 


 * explanation on
 * what you clicked to create the manual approval order
 * how to approve the manual approval order

Will update here once it is clear how to process with the new change.;;;

It can be seen that the unity order tracker on the test2b does not trigger any more updates for the order after the one with the status OPEN (for which we already have a customer ID as seen in the log).

I checked the test2b database contains the UME_ORDER_STATUS 'COMPLETED', which is correct, but apparently not written by the unity order tracker. Maybe there is a race condition between the unity order tracker and some other service that tries to write this field? This would also explain why it only happens sometimes.;;;
